<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 10:42PM CDT  by NWS Midland-Odessa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Mitchell, western Scurry, eastern Borden and northeastern Howard
Counties through 1130 PM CDT...
At 1042 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fluvanna, or 13 miles west of Snyder, moving south at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Fluvanna, J B Thomas Reservoir, Vincent and Knapp.
This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 198 and 203.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for western Texas.</instruction>
